name: AI Timesheet Generator with Gmail, Calendar & GitHub to Google Sheets
description:
# AI-Powered Automatic Timesheet Generator for Google Sheets

Stop wasting billable hours on manual time-tracking. **AutoTimesheet Pro** uses AI to collect emails, meetings, and GitHub work, then writes a clean timesheet straight into Google Sheets. Perfect for developers, consultants, agencies, and remote teams.

---

## üöÄ Key Features

- **Automated Google Sheets time-tracking** ‚Äî zero spreadsheet prep.  
- **AI-generated activity summaries** (‚â§ 120 chars) via OpenAI GPT-4o-mini.  
- **Gmail integration** ‚Äî logs only important emails, skipping newsletters & no-replies.  
- **Google Calendar time logger** ‚Äî captures confirmed events, duration, and attendees.  
- **GitHub commit & PR tracker** ‚Äî records your commits plus opened/closed PRs.  
- **Daily 7 PM cron trigger** (easily adjustable).  
- **Month-based sheet creation** ‚Äî new tab spins up on the first run each month.  
- **No-code n8n template** ‚Äî just connect credentials and tweak one **Set Variables** node.
- **üîå Easily extensible** ‚Äî drag-and-drop extra n8n nodes to add Slack, Jira, Notion, Asana, Trello, Toggl, or any other data source you need.

---

## üîç How It Works

1. **Collect** ‚Äî n8n pulls data from Gmail, Google Calendar, and chosen GitHub repos.  
2. **Clean** ‚Äî filters remove noise (newsletters, irrelevant commits, etc.).  
3. **Condense** ‚Äî OpenAI rewrites each item into a concise, SEO-friendly description.  
4. **Write** ‚Äî workflow appends *Date*, *Type*, and *Description* to your **Timesheet** Google Sheet.
5. **Extend** ‚Äî simply insert new n8n nodes (e.g., Slack, Notion, Jira) and merge them into the same pipeline.

---

## üìà Benefits for SEO-Minded Professionals

- **Keyword-rich activity log** improves internal search and reporting.  
- **Structured data** in Sheets simplifies export to accounting or PM tools.  
- **Consistent naming** (`CALENDAR_EVENT`, `EMAIL`, `COMMIT`, `PR`) makes analytics easy.

---

## ‚úÖ Why Choose AutoTimesheet Pro?

- Zero manual entry ‚Äî just open the sheet and bill clients.  
- Immediate visibility into where your hours went.  
- Works with any GitHub repo list and any inbox you own.  
- 100 % no-code setup ‚Äî activate in minutes.
- Built on n8n, so you can customize and scale without limits.
---

## üì• Get Started

Ready to replace manual time-tracking with smart automation?  

#### https://n8n.partnerlinks.io/ds9podzjls6d

Join **N8N** now, connect your Google & GitHub accounts, and let AI handle your daily log.

---

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

  ‚Ä¢ github.pullRequests      (array)

TASK
1. Walk through every element in those arrays.
2. For each element create an object that has **exactly**:
     - "type"        : CALENDAR_EVENT | EMAIL | COMMIT | PR
     - "description" : ‚â§120 chars, no commas, no line-breaks
3. Put all objects in one JSON **array**.
4. RETURN  that array. No wrapper object, no markdown. Try to create a nice description for each event

parameters.content:
## üìä Daily Activity Tracker Workflow

**Overview:** This workflow automatically collects your daily activities from multiple sources and creates a comprehensive timesheet in Google Sheets.

**Key Features:**
- üìß Tracks important emails (filters out newsletters & no-reply)
- üìÖ Logs calendar events with duration and attendees
- üíª Records GitHub commits and pull requests
- ü§ñ Uses AI to generate concise activity descriptions
- üìù Auto-creates monthly sheets and organizes entries

**Configuration:** Update the **Set Variables** node with your:
- GitHub username
- Email address
- Repository names to track

## üîÑ Data Collection Hub

**Sources:**
- **Gmail:** Fetches emails from today (filtered by sender)
- **Google Calendar:** Gets confirmed events from yesterday
- **GitHub API:** Retrieves commits via custom API call
- **GitHub Node:** Pulls all PRs from specified repository

**Note:** Calendar events use yesterday's date (`$today.minus(1)`) - adjust if needed for your timezone

## üîç GitHub Activity Filtering

**Commit Filter:**
- Only includes commits by the configured user
- Fetches commits from yesterday (UTC)

**PR Filters:**
1. **Created Today:** New PRs opened by the user
2. **Closed Today:** PRs that were merged/closed

**Purpose:** Ensures only relevant GitHub activity is tracked in the timesheet

## üìã Sheet Management

**Monthly Sheet Creation:**
- Automatically creates a new sheet for each month
- Names sheets using month name (e.g., "January")
- Checks if sheet already exists to avoid duplicates

**Header Row Setup:**
- Creates empty row with Date, Type, Description columns
- Only runs on first execution of the month

## üîÄ Data Aggregation

**Purpose:** Combines multiple items into single data objects

**Aggregate Nodes:**
- **Emails ‚Üí emails[]**
- **Calendar Events ‚Üí calendarEvents[]**
- **Commits ‚Üí commits[]**
- **Pull Requests ‚Üí prs[]**

**Merge Node:** Combines all aggregated data into one payload for AI processing

## üíæ Final Output

**Google Sheets2 Node:**
- Appends each activity to the current month's sheet
- Maps AI-generated data:
  - **Type:** CALENDAR_EVENT | EMAIL | COMMIT | PR
  - **Description:** Concise activity summary
  - **Date:** Today's date (YYYY-MM-DD format)

**Result:** Clean, organized timesheet ready for review!

## ü§ñ AI Processing & Summary

**Purpose:** Transform raw activity data into structured timesheet entries

**Process:**
1. **Format All Data** node consolidates data from all sources
2. **OpenAI GPT-4o-mini** generates concise descriptions (‚â§120 chars)
3. **Split Out** node separates individual events for sheet insertion

**Output:** Clean, categorized entries ready for Google Sheets
